---
version: 3
op: attend.rerank
description: rerank N candidates by relevance to a query, biased toward decision-class content
max_output_tokens: 100
vars: [query, candidates]
---
Rank candidates by relevance to the query. Most relevant FIRST.

Query: {{.query}}

Candidates ("ID [category]: content", input order is arbitrary):
{{.candidates}}

Rules:
- Category strongly biases ranking: decision > constraint > correction > pattern > insight > implementation.
- "Decision" content always outranks "implementation" or "pattern" content on the SAME topic, even when implementation/pattern mentions more keywords.
- Direct off-topic content (different domain entirely) ranks last regardless of category.
- Omit candidates whose topic is clearly unrelated.

Output ONLY a JSON object — no prose, no markdown fence. Reason ≤10 words.

{"ranking": ["id1", "id2", ...], "reason": "≤10 words"}

Example A — query "How should errors be handled?":
  error_pattern [pattern], logging_config [pattern], error_decision [decision]
  → {"ranking":["error_decision","error_pattern"],"reason":"decision wins; logging off-topic"}

Example B — query "What database should we use?":
  db_schema [implementation], db_connection [pattern], db_config_v2 [decision]
  → {"ranking":["db_config_v2","db_schema"],"reason":"decision outranks schema/impl on db-choice question"}
